<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">WITHIN THE BATTLE MAP CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move character / Move map and windows cursors - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Confirm action / Talk to people -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Cancel action / Press for high-speed movement of map cursor -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Search for non-active unit -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Press when the guidance mark is displayed on the lower right of the screen to display a detailed explanation of the cursor movement -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Triangle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Rotate field of view left and right -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;R1 or L1 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Tilt field of view to above/below - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L2 or R2 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Press to view player's units in flashing blue, enemy forces units in flashing red - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Check attack range of the non-active enemies - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font><br>
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">WORLD MAP / CITY CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move window cursor - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Confirm action -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Press when the guidance mark is displayed on the lower right of the screen to display a detailed explanation regarding the content of the cursor location -  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Triangle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Call up the main commands - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font><br><br>
        &nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
